        " : «مَنْ مَاتَ وَ لَمْ يَكُنْ لَهُ هَدْيٌ لِمُتْعَتِهِ فَلْيَصُمْ عَنْهُ وَلِيُّهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3097 - Safwan narrated from Muawiyah ibn Ammar, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"If a person dies and does not have a hady (sacrificial animal) for his Tamattu', his guardian should fast on his behalf.\""
